POLIOMYELITIS UPDATE (71): GLOBAL (PAKISTAN, DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO)
******************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 30 Aug 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative / WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update, as of 29 Aug 2019, World Health Organization
--------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 5
Environment: 0

Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2019: 71
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 33

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 6
Environment: 1
Others: 2

Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2019: 59
Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2018: 104

Headlines
- Technical Advisory Group on Polio Eradication in Afghanistan met on 25-26 Aug 2019 to discuss and propose recommendations on a range of thematic areas in combatting the ongoing wild poliovirus transmission in the region, including: access issues, ban on house-to-house campaigns, optimizing community engagement, and geographic prioritization.

Summary of new viruses this week:
- Pakistan - 5 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases;
- Nigeria - 1 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2)-positive healthy contact sample;
- Democratic Republic of the Congo - 6 cVDPV2 cases;
- Ghana - 1 cVDPV2-positive environmental sample.

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case has been reported in the past week. There are 13 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.
- No WPV1-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week.

Pakistan
- 5 wild polioviruses type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported in the past week: 1 each from Hangu, Bannu, and North Waziristan districts, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province; and, 2 from Hyderabad district, Sindh province. The onsets of paralysis were on [28 Jul 2019, 2 Aug 2019, 21 Jul 2019, 20 Jul 2019, and 5 Aug 2019] respectively. There are 58 WPV1 cases in 2019, and 12 WPV1 cases were reported in 2018.
- No WPV1-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week.

Nigeria
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in the past week. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.
- 1 cVDPV2-positive healthy contact sample was reported in the past week from Ibaji district, Kogi province. The sample was collected on [24 Jul 2019].

Lake Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been reported in the past week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018), and Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord).
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Ghana
- No cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case in 2019.
- 1 cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was collected from Accra district, Greater Accra Region. The sample was collected on [13 Aug 2019]. Earlier, a cVDPV2 was isolated from an environment sample collected on [11 Jun 2019] from the Northern province. Both the isolates are linked to the Jigawa cVDPV2 outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.

Benin
- No case of cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case reported in 2019 so far.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- 6 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) have been reported in the past week: 1 each from Djalo-Ndjeka, Vanga-Kete, Katako-Kombe, and Bena-Dibele districts from Sankuru State; 1 from Kilwa district, Katanga State; and, 1 from Mukanga, Haut Lomami State. The onsets of paralysis were on [10 Jul 2019, 18 Jul 2019, 17 Jul 2019, 9 Jul 2019, 29 Jun 2019, and 22 Jun 2019] respectively. There are 23 cases of cVDPV2 reported in 2019. There were 20 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2018. DRC is currently affected by 9 separate cVDPV2 outbreaks; 1 each originated in Haut Katanga, Mongala, Sankuru, Tanganika, Tshuapa, Kasai, Kasai Central, and 2 in Haut Lomami provinces.

Angola
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been reported week in the past week. There are a total of 6 cVDPV2 cases from 3 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic:
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been reported week in past week.
- There are 4 reported cases from 4 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019. Additional confirmed cVDPV2 community contact have been reported in CAR.
- No environmental samples were reported.

Horn of Africa
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been reported in the past week.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3 and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. Circulating VDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in 1 environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There is also 1 reported case of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia, with onset on 20 May 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been reported this week. There was 1 case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) has been reported. There are 3 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 28 Aug 2019:
Total global cases in 2019: 71 (compared with 15 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in endemic countries in 2019: 71 (compared with 15 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in non-endemic countries in 2019: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018)

- Afghanistan: 13 cases in 2019 (compared with 12 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 16 Jul 2019
- Pakistan: 58 cases in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 5 Aug 2019
- Nigeria: 0 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Aug 2016

Total global WPV1 cases in 2019: 71
Total global WPV1 cases in 2018: 33

Officially reported cVDPV cases as of 28 Aug 2019
- Angola: 6 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 12 Jul 2019
- Benin: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 30 Jun 2019
- Central African Republic: 4 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 23 Jun 2019
- China: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 25 Apr 2019
- Democratic Republic of the Congo: 23 cases in 2019 (compared with 13 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 18 Jul 2019
- Ethiopia: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 20 May 2019
- Ghana: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 23 Jul 2019
- Indonesia (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 27 Nov 2018
- Mozambique: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Oct 2018
- Myanmar (type 1): 3 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 14 Jun 2019
- Niger: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 3 Apr 2019
- Nigeria: 15 cases in 2019 (compared with 8 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 20 Jun 2019
- Papua New Guinea (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 18 Oct 2018
- Somalia (type 2): 3 cases in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 8 May 2019
- Somalia (type 3): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 7 Sep 2018

Total global cVDPV cases in 2019: 59
Total global cVDPV cases in 2018: 104

